phy information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384658","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-25","<p>My Department has not estimated the economic benefits from tourists visiting the Palace of Westminster. However, according to Visitor Services at the Houses of Parliament, over 1 million people visit the Parliamentary Estate each year, on average 200,000 of which are during Parliament's commercial openings on Saturdays and during recess periods. We understand that details of income generated from parliamentary commercial visitors will be published in the forthcoming House of Commons Commission annual report.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-06-25T14:12:08.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384658/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384658/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-22","Palace of Westminster: Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the benefit to the economy from tourists visiting the Palace of Westminster.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","3537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384659","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>The most recent Ministry of Defence Police deployment to Pitcairn Island, which was at the request of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, concluded on 14 February 2007.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:10:10.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384659/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384659/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Pitcairn Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when an officer of the Ministry of Defence Police last visited the Pitcairn Islands.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384660","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>There are no existing wind farms or current applications pending on Ministry of Defence land, as they would have an impact on military capability.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3527","2015-06-25T15:23:56.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384660/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384660/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many onshore windfarms are situated on Ministry of Defence land; and where each such wind farm is based.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384661","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>There are no existing wind farms or current applications pending on Ministry of Defence land, as they would have an impact on military capability.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3526","2015-06-25T15:23:57.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384661/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384661/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what planning applications for windfarms in what locations on Ministry of Defence land are pending.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384662","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>None of the non-executive directors in post prior to May 2015 have since left the Department's Defence Board.</p><p>Since May 2010 there has been one extension and four new appointments to the Defence Board by the Secretary of State for Defence:</p><p>Mrs Priscilla Vacassin - Defence Board Non-Executive Director (extended in post in 2010).</p><p>Sir Gerry Grimstone - Lead Non-Executive Director for the Ministry of Defence.</p><p>Mr Graham Williams - Defence Board Non-Executive Director.</p><p>Mr Paul Skinner - Defence Board Non-Executive Director.</p><p>Mrs Danuta Gray - Defence Board Non-Executive Director.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-29T15:27:19.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384662/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384662/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Ministry of Defence: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many non-executive directors of his Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments he has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384663","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>We strongly condemn Monday's attack on Afghan democracy.</p><p>The Afghan security forces responded positively to the incident and secured the Parliamentary site. They have held lead responsibility for security across Afghanistan since July 2013.</p><p>Alongside partners , the UK continues to make an important contribution to advising Afghanistan on security development through NATO's mission. The UK's focus is on institutional capacity building, including supporting the training of the next generation of Afghan Army officers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-29T15:29:16.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384663/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384663/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Afghanistan: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what additional military training or assistance is being offered to the government of Afghanistan following the recent attack on the Afghan Parliament.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","3500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384664","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>Our records show that 22 Service personnel travelled to Colombia during 2014 for visits designed to further the defence relationship with Colombia through: defence education; transformation of the Colombian defence organisation; international law and post-conflict transition. In addition HMS Richmond, HMS Portland and HMS Argyll visited Colombia during 2014.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-29T15:30:19.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384664/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384664/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Colombia: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces personnel travelled to Colombia in 2014.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","3588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384665","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>Dstl returns the numbers of procedures involving animals to the Home Office on an annual basis in accordance with UK legislation. Figures for 2015 will not be available until after the returns have been made. Details of the Annual Dstl Returns to the Home Office for calendar year 2014 are given in the table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Animal species (type)</p></td><td><p>Mouse</p></td><td><p>Rat</p></td><td><p>Guinea Pigs</p></td><td><p>Pigs</p></td><td><p>Non-Human Primate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number</p></td><td><p>3,411</p></td><td><p>223</p></td><td><p>323</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Every procedure is undertaken in strict accordance with the terms of the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986; and Dstl fully embraces the principles of the 3Rs (Replacement, Reduction and Refinement). Dstl Porton Down is licensed by the Home Office to conduct research involving animals.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","3597","2015-06-25T16:42:36.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384665/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384665/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many experiments were carried out by his Department on each animal species in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384666","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>Dstl returns the numbers of procedures involving animals to the Home Office on an annual basis in accordance with UK legislation. Figures for 2015 will not be available until after the returns have been made. Details of the Annual Dstl Returns to the Home Office for calendar year 2014 are given in the table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Animal species (type)</p></td><td><p>Mouse</p></td><td><p>Rat</p></td><td><p>Guinea Pigs</p></td><td><p>Pigs</p></td><td><p>Non-Human Primate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Number</p></td><td><p>3,411</p></td><td><p>223</p></td><td><p>323</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>67</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Every procedure is undertaken in strict accordance with the terms of the Animals (Scientific Procedures) Act 1986; and Dstl fully embraces the principles of the 3Rs (Replacement, Reduction and Refinement). Dstl Porton Down is licensed by the Home Office to conduct research involving animals.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","3596","2015-06-25T16:42:36.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384666/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384666/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Animal Experiments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what animal species were used by his Department in experiments in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384667","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 23 June 2015 to Question 3199 to the hon. Member for Bridgend (Mrs Moon).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-06-25T15:30:32.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384667/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384667/answer","20150623_3199_QnA_extract[1].doc","20150623_3199_QnA_extract[1].doc","20150623 - QnA extract to 3199","20150623 - QnA extract to 3199","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384667/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-22","Libya: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to publish his Department's report, undertaken in December 2014, on the training of Libyan soldiers at Bassingbourn Barracks and subsequent attacks in Cambridge.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","3604"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384668","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>The Government wants all young people to leave school prepared for life in modern Britain. We agree with the Committee that high-quality physical, social, health and economic education (PSHE) and sex and relationships education (SRE) has a vital role to play in this. We are carefully considering the Committee’s recommendations and how best to address this.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-06-25T14:28:30.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384668/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384668/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","Personal, Social, Health and Economic Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to respond to the Fifth Report of the Education Committee, Session 2014-15, HC 145 on Life Lessons: PSHE and SRE in schools.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","3595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384669","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>The government is committed to increasing the number of young people studying STEM subjects, in particular the number of girls.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, A level entries by female students have risen in all STEM subjects: in maths by 8%, in further maths by 8%, in biology by 12%, in chemistry by19% and in physics by15%.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Schools have the freedom to decide how to use this funding in the way that best suits the needs of their pupils. During the last five years, the department has funded four <del> </del>initiatives specifically aimed at increasing the study of STEM subjects by girls.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Stimulating Physics Network aims to increase the number of students progressing to A Level physics, with an emphasis on girls. Since 2010, the Network has received the following funding; 2010-11 £1.3m; 2011-12 £1.3m; 2012-13 £1.85m; 2013-14 £1.85m; 2014-15 £2.1m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Further Mathematics Support Programme aims to increase the number of students studying A Level Mathematics and Further Mathematics, again with an emphasis on girls. Since 2011, the programme has received the following funding: 2010-11 £1.5m; 2011-12 - £1.75m; 2012-13 - £3.25m; 2013-14 - £3.5m; 2014-15 £5m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Big Bang Near Me activities are local versions of the national Big Bang Fair and reach more than 80,000 young people, achieving a 50:50 split of boys and girls. Since 2011, the programme has received the following funding: 2010-11 £0.15m; 2011-12 - £0.15m; 2012-13 - £0.15m; 2013-14 - £0.15m; 2014-15 - £0.15m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Your Life campaign launched by the government in 2014 aims to increase the numbers taking A Level physics and maths, particularly girls. The government spent £600,000 on Your Life activity in 2014-15. The campaign is now independently run and funded.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","3583","2015-06-25T13:31:49.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384669/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384669/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","STEM Subjects: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to increase the study of STEM subjects by women; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384670","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>The government is committed to increasing the number of young people studying STEM subjects, in particular the number of girls.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2010, A level entries by female students have risen in all STEM subjects: in maths by 8%, in further maths by 8%, in biology by 12%, in chemistry by19% and in physics by15%.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Schools have the freedom to decide how to use this funding in the way that best suits the needs of their pupils. During the last five years, the department has funded four <del> </del>initiatives specifically aimed at increasing the study of STEM subjects by girls.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Stimulating Physics Network aims to increase the number of students progressing to A Level physics, with an emphasis on girls. Since 2010, the Network has received the following funding; 2010-11 £1.3m; 2011-12 £1.3m; 2012-13 £1.85m; 2013-14 £1.85m; 2014-15 £2.1m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Further Mathematics Support Programme aims to increase the number of students studying A Level Mathematics and Further Mathematics, again with an emphasis on girls. Since 2011, the programme has received the following funding: 2010-11 £1.5m; 2011-12 - £1.75m; 2012-13 - £3.25m; 2013-14 - £3.5m; 2014-15 £5m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Big Bang Near Me activities are local versions of the national Big Bang Fair and reach more than 80,000 young people, achieving a 50:50 split of boys and girls. Since 2011, the programme has received the following funding: 2010-11 £0.15m; 2011-12 - £0.15m; 2012-13 - £0.15m; 2013-14 - £0.15m; 2014-15 - £0.15m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Your Life campaign launched by the government in 2014 aims to increase the numbers taking A Level physics and maths, particularly girls. The government spent £600,000 on Your Life activity in 2014-15. The campaign is now independently run and funded.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","3582","2015-06-25T13:31:49.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384670/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384670/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","STEM Subjects: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what funding her Department has made available to increase the study of STEM subjects by women in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384671","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>In January 2015, 77 students living in Scotland were educated in schools in England. This information is published in the schools, pupils and characteristics statistical first release[1].</p><p> </p><p>As residents of the UK, those living in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland have a right to apply for a place in an English state school. If they have priority for admission under the school’s admissions policy they must be admitted. It is unlikely that many children living outside of England will have priority for admission to English schools, as most schools prioritise pupils living close by. These rights are reciprocal, and English residents can apply for Scottish, Welsh or Northern Irish schools.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2015</a> (Tables 14a to 14c)</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-06-25T13:23:55.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384671/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384671/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","Pupils: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children live in Scotland and go to school in England.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","3510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384672","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>One non-executive board member has left the Department’s board since May 2015: My Noble Friend the Lord O’Neill of Gatley was a non-executive board member for one year and eight months and resigned on his appointment as Commercial Secretary to the Treasury. Sir Theodore Agnew resigned from the Department’s board in March 2015 after four years and eight months in post.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>My Rt Hon Friend, the Member for Loughborough Nicky Morgan, appointed Marion Plant OBE as non-executive board member for the Department for Education in January 2015.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-06-25T13:26:51.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384672/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384672/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","Department for Education: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many non-executive directors of her Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments she has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384673","Department for Education","false","2015-06-25","<p>Many schools already choose to include cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and defibrillator awareness as part of their personal, social, health and economic education (PSHE) teaching, using the services of organisations such as the Red Cross and St John Ambulance.</p><p> </p><p>The British Heart Foundation has offered to provide free CPR training kits to every secondary school in the country, allowing young people to gain first-hand experience of this important life-saving skill. We have used our social media channels to raise awareness of this resource and have agreed to work with the British Heart Foundation to continue to promote this kit to schools. We expect many schools to take up this offer.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-06-25T12:44:24.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384673/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384673/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","First Aid: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent steps she has taken to promote cardiopulmonary resuscitation in schools.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","3525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384674","Department for Education","false","2015-06-30","<p>An Academy Order was issued because the Hewett School is a failing school which Ofsted judged to require special measures in October 2014 and has had GCSE results consistently below local and national averages for the past five years. The Academy Order was issued on 25 March after consultation with the central Norwich Foundation Trust. The Government’s policy is to tackle swiftly failing schools wherever they are. We believe that the best way to secure rapid and long-term improvement at the Hewett School is for it to become an academy with the support of a strong sponsor. Inspiration Trust was the named sponsor due to its strong track record of school improvement.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education and Norfolk County Council meet regularly. Recently the Council’s proposals for a ‘Learning Village’ on the Hewett site have formed part of these discussions. The department has had an initial meeting with the Inspiration Trust to seek their views about the future of the land. A meeting between all three parties is scheduled later this month.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","3507","2015-06-30T13:03:50.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384674/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384674/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","Hewett School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many times her Department has met (a) Norfolk County Council and (b) the Inspiration Trust to discuss the land on which the Hewlett School sits in Norwich South.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","3446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384675","Department for Education","false","2015-06-30","<p>An Academy Order was issued because the Hewett School is a failing school which Ofsted judged to require special measures in October 2014 and has had GCSE results consistently below local and national averages for the past five years. The Academy Order was issued on 25 March after consultation with the central Norwich Foundation Trust. The Government’s policy is to tackle swiftly failing schools wherever they are. We believe that the best way to secure rapid and long-term improvement at the Hewett School is for it to become an academy with the support of a strong sponsor. Inspiration Trust was the named sponsor due to its strong track record of school improvement.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education and Norfolk County Council meet regularly. Recently the Council’s proposals for a ‘Learning Village’ on the Hewett site have formed part of these discussions. The department has had an initial meeting with the Inspiration Trust to seek their views about the future of the land. A meeting between all three parties is scheduled later this month.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","3446","2015-06-30T13:03:50.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384675/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384675/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-22","Hewett School","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, for what reasons she exercised an academy order under section 4 of the Academies Act 2010 in appointing a sponsor for the Hewett School in Norwich.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","3507"
