"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384759","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-02","<p>I was appointed as Secretary of State for Scotland on the 15 May 2015. None of the Non-Executive Directors who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department’s Board. The previous Secretary of State for Scotland approved the following Non-Executive appointments to the Scotland Office and Office of the Advocate General’s Joint Management Board on the 20 March 2015:</p><p>Graeme Bissett</p><p>Joyce Cullen</p><p>Shonaig Macpherson</p><p>Details regarding the Joint Management Board can be found in the Offices’ annual report and accounts, which are published on GOV.UK. The Offices’ annual report for 2014-2015 will be laid in the UK Parliament shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-02T14:26:50.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384759/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384759/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-06-22","Scotland Office: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many non-executive directors of his Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments he has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384760","Scotland Office","false","2015-06-30","<p>As part of the Scotland Analysis programme, which was completed in 2014, it was calculated that each day, around 16,500 people cross the Scottish border to work in the rest of the UK, while 13,000 people travel the other way.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-06-30T11:53:09.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384760/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384760/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-06-22","Employment: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many people who live in Scotland work in England.","false","Biography information for John Stevenson","Carlisle","John Stevenson","3578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384761","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-30","<p>The two-year appointment of one non-executive, John Kirkland, expired in June. No appointments or re-appointments have yet been made.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-30T10:53:27.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384761/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384761/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Department for Transport: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many non-executive directors of his Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments he has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384762","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>The Shareholder Executive submitted its review to me in early March, in the last months of the previous Parliament.</p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-06-25T15:53:24.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384762/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384762/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2015 to Question 1550, on what date he received the Stakeholder Executive's review of Network Rail's governance.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384763","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Department for Transport published statistics on travel costs, based on data from the Office for National Statistics (ONS), in the Transport Statistics Great Britain compendium.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Data from the independent ONS suggests that:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(i) Between 1980 and 2014</p><p> </p><p>a) the real cost of motoring, including the purchase of a vehicle, declined by 14%,</p><p> </p><p>b) bus and coach fares increased by 58% and</p><p> </p><p>c) rail fares increased by 63% in real terms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(ii) Between 1997 and 2014</p><p> </p><p>a) the real cost of motoring, including the purchase of a vehicle, declined by 11%,</p><p> </p><p>b) bus and coach fares increased by 27% and</p><p> </p><p>c) rail fares increased by 24% in real terms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(iii) Between 2010 and 2014</p><p> </p><p>a) the real cost of motoring, including the purchase of a vehicle, decreased by 5%,</p><p> </p><p>b) bus and coach fares increased by 2% and</p><p> </p><p>c) rail fares increased by 6% in real terms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(d) The costs of travelling by air are not available from ONS data.　 However information is available based on fare data from the Civil Aviation Authority from 2000. The real cost of the average UK one-way air fare, including taxes and charges, covering domestic flights from 2010 to 2013 declined by 4%. Estimates for 2014 are not yet available.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-29T10:08:32.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384763/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384763/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Travel: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the percentage change in real terms of the cost to the traveller of travelling by (a) private car, (b) bus, (c) train and (d) domestic aeroplane since (i) 1980, (ii) 1997 and (iii) 2010.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","3443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384764","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government announced last year financial support for two public service obligation routes, Dundee – London City and Newquay Cornwall – London Gatwick from the Regional Air Connectivity Fund.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to this the Government undertook earlier this year an initial application stage for airlines to bid for start-up aid funding. The Government will announce after the July Budget how we will take this forward.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-29T09:25:15.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384764/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384764/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Regional Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the reason is for the time taken to allocate funding under the Regional Air Connectivity Fund; and when an announcement of the launch of the new air links under the Fund will be made.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","3445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384765","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Child fares are defined at 15 not only in rail, but most other forms of public transport. The definition for child fares on rail is set out in the National Rail Conditions of Carriage (NRCoC). This states that states that &quot;Children under 16 years of age are entitled to discounts on most tickets.&quot; The NRCoC is an agreement between train operators that sets out arrangements for the carriage of passengers and the retailing of tickets. As such any changes to this agreement would need to be for train operators to consider and not the department.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-29T10:21:48.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384765/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384765/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Railways: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to raise the child rail fare age limit from 15 to 18.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","3438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384766","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>The spend on the SEFT programme each year has been:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>2015/2016 (as of 1 June 2015): £1.6m</p><p> </p><p>2014/2015: £16.5m</p><p> </p><p>2013/2014: £8.2m</p><p> </p><p>2012/2013: £1.5m</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No funding has been transferred from the ITSO on Prestige programme to SEFT.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-25T12:01:04.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384766/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384766/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Railways: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 2610, what his Department's annual expenditure on the South East Flexible Ticketing programme (SEFT) has been; and what the value was of the funding that was transferred from the ITSO on Prestige programme to SEFT.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384767","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>The rolling stock sector is a private market but the Government has already made its position clear on Pacer trains.</p><p> </p><p>It would be for the Scottish Government, and from 2018, the Welsh Assembly to make such a decision with regard to their transport needs.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-06-25T12:12:29.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384767/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384767/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015 to Question 3009, whether all Pacer trains will be withdrawn from service once they are displaced from the Northern and Great Western franchises.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384768","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-25","<p>The Government has committed to delivering the National Infrastructure Plan alongside a commitment to invest over £100 billion of public spending over the course of this Parliament.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-06-25T15:12:02.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384768/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384768/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-22","Transport: Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will ensure that the National Infrastructure Plan of 2014 is implemented in full.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","3453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384769","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>The information is as follows:-</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Staff in Traffic Officer Service</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>1727</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>1676</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1608</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1516</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>1439</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015 (Highways England)</p></td><td><p>1454</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Please note we have interpreted Traffic Officer Service as Traffic Officers and support staff such as control room staff.</p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>Note that the decrease in the number of staff in the Traffic Officer Service reflects various organisational changes which have not impacted on the operational capability of the service: such as the introduction of Flexible Rostering into the Traffic Officer Service which has meant less staff are required to operate; and a review of the Team Manager role has lead to non-operational tasks removed from the role and posts converted into non-operational roles in Service Delivery, a department not in the Traffic Officer Service.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-25T09:41:26.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384769/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384769/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Traffic Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people were employed in the Highways Agency Traffic Officer Service in each year since 2010; and how many people are employed in the comparable section of Highways England.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","3454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384770","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Since the abolition of the tax disc the there has been a small increase in the number of unlicensed vehicles being used on the road which has led to more vehicles being clamped. This is due to a small subsection of motorists buying vehicles but not taxing them immediately as required. The DVLA has written to all those identified to remind them of the need to tax their vehicle.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-29T09:42:25.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384770/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384770/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Immobilisation of Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2015 to Question 2297, what the reasons are for the recent increase in the number of vehicles clamped by other authorities.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","3517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384771","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>To ensure our long term connectivity needs can be met, the previous Government established the independent Airports Commission to identify and recommend to Government options for maintaining this country’s status as an international hub for aviation. Three options for expansion have been shortlisted by the Commission for further examination.</p><p>The Airports Commission has discussed and consulted on how airports outside the South East might be affected by expansion at the shortlisted expansion options. The relevant documents can be found on the Airports Commission website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/airports-commission" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/airports-commission</a></p><p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The Commission’s final report will be published shortly and the Government will carefully consider all the evidence before making a decision on the way forward.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-06-25T11:56:21.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384771/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384771/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Manchester Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect on Manchester Airport of a new runway at (a) Heathrow and (b) Gatwick Airport.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","3538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384772","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>Officials in the Department for Transport’s Rail Executive continually consider a range of medium- to long-term policy issues relating to rail infrastructure management and connected issues covering the wider rail industry. 　In so doing, and to ensure the robustness of their work, they engage with internal and external stakeholders on a regular basis.</p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-06-25T15:59:26.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384772/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384772/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the purpose is of his Department's Rail Infrastructure Futures unit; on what date that unit was created; how many officials work in the Rail Infrastructure Futures team; and whether any external bodies have seconded staff to that unit or undertaken work at Rail Infrastructure Futures' request.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384773","Wales Office","false","2015-06-26","<p>The Wales Office has two non-executive directors. One of the non-executive directors (David Crawley) stood down on 31 March 2015 after serving 9 years 3 months. The Wales Office has appointed one non-executive director since May 2010; this appointment was made on 1 April 2015.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2015-06-26T12:10:28.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384773/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384773/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2015-06-22","Wales Office: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many non-executive directors of his Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments he has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384774","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-26","<p /> <p>One non-executive director, Willy Roe, was in post before May 2015 and has since left the Department’s board. His tenure was from 01 July 2011 to 30 June 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Details of non-executive appointments are included in the Department’s published annual reports and accounts. Since May 2010, 6 individuals have been appointed to the Department’s board. Their names and tenures are as follow:</p><p> </p><p>John Clare: 01 November 2011 to 31 October 2012</p><p>Ian Cheshire: 01 February 2011 to 10 November 2014</p><p>Willy Roe: 01 July 2011 to 30 June 2015</p><p>Dame Clara Furse: 01 July 2011 to date</p><p>David Lister: 01 July 2011 to date</p><p>Andrew Graham: 12 March 2015 to date</p><p> </p><p>Currently, we have 3 non-executive directors on the board.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-26T14:00:47.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384774/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384774/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-22","Department for Work and Pensions: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many non-executive directors of his Department who were in post before May 2015 have since left the Department's board; what the names and length of tenure of such directors were; and how many and what non-executive director appointments he has made since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3568"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384775","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-30","<p /> <p>Since Personal Independence Payment was rolled out from April 2013, 2,134 claimants have been sent home because the number of claimants attending scheduled appointments exceeds expectations. This represents 0.4% of the total number of claimants seen. This information is sourced from Atos and Capita Management Information records and has not been quality assured.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-30T15:52:38.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384775/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384775/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-22","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many personal independence payment assessment appointments failed to take place as a result of double booking of appointments between 2010 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","3516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384776","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-25","<p>From April 2013 (when the benefit cap was introduced) to February 2015 (the latest available data) 1,876 single parent households with one child dependant have been capped. Of these, 1,158 households (62%) have a child aged under 5 as at February 2015.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the number of children aged under 5 is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3367 ; 3368 ; 3369 ; 3458","2015-06-25T16:27:15.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384776/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384776/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-22","Social Security Benefits: Lone Parents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of lone parent families with two children affected by the benefit cap have (a) one child and (b) two children aged under five.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384777","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-25","<p>From April 2013 (when the benefit cap was introduced) to February 2015 (the latest available data) 1,876 single parent households with one child dependant have been capped. Of these, 1,158 households (62%) have a child aged under 5 as at February 2015.</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the number of children aged under 5 is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3367 ; 3368 ; 3369 ; 3459","2015-06-25T16:27:15.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384777/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384777/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-22","Social Security Benefits: Lone Parents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of lone parent families with three children affected by the benefit cap have (a) one child, (b) two children and (c) three children aged under five.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384933","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-08-28","<p>Government has a range of measures in place to support deployment of low carbon energy sources. For electricity, these include Contracts for Difference, which will provide efficient long term support for all forms of low carbon electricity generation. <br> <br>For heat, the non-domestic and domestic Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI) schemes are designed to bridge the gap between the cost of fossil fuel heat sources and renewable alternatives through financial support for owners of participating installations in Great Britain.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-08-28T13:55:42.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384933/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384933/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-22","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps her Department is taking to incentivise greater use of renewable and non-fossil fuel forms of energy.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","900543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384948","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-25","<p>Adaptation to climate change is an integral part of policy across all levels of government (for example, the £3.2bn floods programme and work to build resilience across the health and transport sectors).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Climate Change Act 2008 has put in place a five-year adaptation policy and research cycle in which the Government first assesses the risks and opportunities facing the UK from climate change based on the latest available evidence, and then produces a policy programme to address those risks. Work on the next risk assessment, to be completed in 2017, is well underway.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In producing the Climate Change Risk Assessment and National Adaptation Programme, Defra officials continually engage with a wide range of interests active in this area, including the Adaptation Sub-Committee of the Committee on Climate Change, Defra’s Science Advisory Council and Economic Advisory Panel, Research Councils, Innovate UK and the Aldersgate Group.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2015-06-25T15:13:34.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384948/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384948/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-22","Climate Change: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to support research and innovation in adaptation to climate change.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","900553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385139","Department for Transport","false","2015-06-25","<p>Cars, vans and heavy good vehicles emit greenhouse gases, including carbon dioxide, which contribute to climate change.</p><p /> <p>Each year the Government publishes updated energy projections analysing and projecting future greenhouse gas emissions in the UK.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>The last set of data was published in September 2014 and projects a reduction in road transport emissions over the period 2015 to 2020 from 108 Mt CO2 to 99 Mt CO2, based on current committed policy.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p /> <p>The UK has some of the most stretching carbon targets in the world which will see a 50% reduction in greenhouse gas emissions in 2025 compared to 1990 levels, on a path towards an 80% reduction by 2050.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-06-25T11:49:14.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385139/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385139/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-22","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of automotive emissions on climate change in the next five years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","900550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385637","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-25","<p>Good progress has been made. The industry is making extensive preparations in the areas of meter procurement; in building and testing their systems, and in staff recruitment and training. Consumers are already benefiting from the roll-out – around 1.5 million meters are operating under the Programme – putting consumers in control of their energy use, bringing an end to estimated bills, and helping people to save energy and money.</p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2015-06-25T15:01:06.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385637/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385637/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-22","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what progress she has made on the rollout of smart meters.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","900556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385638","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-25","<p>The scale of investment required in large renewable generation projects needs private sector leadership. However, the department is keen to work in partnership with industry for example, to suppport the development of new and innovative technologies. We're currently using procurement to drive innovation and are working with more than 100 companies on energy innovation projects.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-25T14:59:34.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385638/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385638/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-22","Renewable Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what steps she is taking to maximise renewable energy generation through public procurement.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","900551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385639","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-25","<p>As I said in response to the honourable members’ questions on this subject already, securing a global climate deal in Paris is a key priority for me.</p><p> </p><p>The G7 recently made great progress in setting out what is needed for this deal, particularly on climate finance. They committed to continue efforts to provide and mobilise increased finance, from public and private sources, and to demonstrate that we are well on our way to meet the goal of US $100 billion flowing to developing countries by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is, of course, already playing a leadership role through our £3.87bn International Climate Fund, through which we are delivering real world impacts in some of the most vulnerable countries in the world.</p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2015-06-25T14:57:48.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385639/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385639/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-22","Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what progress is being made on reaching an international climate change agreement in Paris.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","900542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384165","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Department does not have any plans, at this time, to fit land-attack missiles to the Type 45 destroyers.</p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-06-30T15:22:32.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384165/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384165/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-19","Type 45 Destroyers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to fit land-attack missiles to T45 destroyers to augment the planned number of F-35B Sea Lightnings available for initial air campaign operations.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384167","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-07-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence, in collaboration with The Royal British Legion, will lead national commemorations in central London on Saturday 15 August 2015 to mark the 70th Anniversary of Victory over Japan Day (VJ Day 70).</p><p>The event will begin with a special commemoration on Horse Guards Parade, attended by senior political and military representatives, veterans and their families, which will include at its heart a traditional Drumhead Service. Current members of the Armed Forces will then lead veterans and their families in a parade down Whitehall, past the Cenotaph and the statue of Field Marshal Lord Slim, who famously led the 14th Army.</p><p>Further details of the VJ Day 70 programme will be announced in due course.</p><p>Invitations to participate in VJ Day 70 have been issued to representatives from all declared allies of the UK, Commonwealth countries, overseas territories and Crown Dependencies. In this way, the contribution and sacrifices made during the Far East campaign by communities such as the Burmese hill tribes will be recognised on this milestone anniversary.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-07-01T10:45:38.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384167/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384167/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-19","VJ Day","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether any representatives of the Burmese hill tribes will attend commemorations of the 70th anniversary of the Victory over Japan Day.","false","Biography information for Lord West of Spithead",,"Lord West of Spithead","HL660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384169","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-29","<p>Burma's elections in November are a milestone in its transition to democracy, and we have consistently called for democratic, inclusive, credible and transparent elections in which all the people of Burma, including persons belonging to minorities, can fully exercise their political rights and cast their vote. This was reiterated in the EU Foreign Affairs Council conclusions on 22 June. However, there are significant challenges in holding Burma’s first credible elections in decades. The withdrawal of temporary residence cards for Rohingya Muslims is a major concern. We have also long made clear that the military should step back from politics. In assessing the overall standard of the election, we will look at these and a range of other factors, including the assessments of both local and international observers on the ground at the time. The UK has supported the EU in sending an Election Observation Mission to observe the elections.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-06-29T13:22:06.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384169/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384169/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-19","Burma: Elections","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of whether the forthcoming elections in Burma can be free and fair, in the light of the withdrawal of temporary voting rights given to Rohingya Muslims and the fact that the military is allocated one quarter of seats.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384171","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-01","<p>Details of the proportion of tuberculosis cases in (1) South Africa, (2) Tanzania, (3) Uganda, (4) Zambia, (5) Zimbabwe, occurring in people living with HIV are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p><strong>HIV-positive TB patients 2013</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Country</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Africa</p></td><td><p>181 736</p></td><td><p>62</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tanzania</p></td><td><p>20 320</p></td><td><p>37</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Uganda</p></td><td><p>20 648</p></td><td><p>48</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Zambia</p></td><td><p>25 476</p></td><td><p>62</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Zimbabwe</p></td><td><p>22 442</p></td><td><p>69</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Tuberculosis country profiles can be found on the World Health Organization (WHO) website.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-07-01T15:58:39.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384171/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384171/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-19","Africa: Tuberculosis","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made, if any, of the proportion of tuberculosis cases in (1) South Africa, (2) Tanzania, (3) Uganda, (4) Zambia, (5) Zimbabwe occurring in people living with HIV.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384173","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-03","<p>As a result of the Northern Ireland Assembly’s inability to pass welfare reform legislation, the Northern Ireland Executive’s allocation has been reduced by £13m in 2013-14, £87m in 2014-15 and £114m in 2015-16 to offset foregone cost savings which would otherwise have accrued. The Executive have been aware of the level of the deduction since March 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Following the exceptional access to the reserve granted to the Northern Ireland Executive in 2014-15, the Executive’s 2015-16 allocation has been reduced by £100m in 2015-16 in accordance with normal budgetary procedures.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These deductions will be reflected in the control totals published alongside departmental Main Supply Estimates for 2015-16.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-07-03T12:05:13.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384173/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384173/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-19","Block Grant: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what effect the failure to pass the Welfare Reform Bill in Northern Ireland has had, in financial terms, on the block grant to Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Hay of Ballyore",,"Lord Hay of Ballyore","HL663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384175","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-06-29","<p>The failure to implement welfare reform puts the entire Stormont House Agreement at risk, including the steps it contains to pave the way for a more stable and prosperous Northern Ireland and to help deal with the past.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2015-06-29T12:23:03.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384175/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384175/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-06-19","Welfare State: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the impact of welfare reform not being agreed in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Lord Hay of Ballyore",,"Lord Hay of Ballyore","HL664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384177","Department for International Development","false","2015-07-01","<p>According to UN reporting, a prolonged dry spell from mid-April to early June has led to soil moisture deficits, particularly in the central and southern provinces of North Korea, resulting in reductions of the 2015 staple rice crop and adversely affecting yield potential of early-planted crops, including maize and soybeans. A detailed assessment of the crop damage is not yet available, but early official estimates provided by the National Coordinating Committee (NCC), as of 8 June, indicate a severe contraction for rice plantings and large cultivated areas adversely affected by the current dry spell.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-07-01T15:59:17.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384177/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384177/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-06-19","North Korea: Droughts","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the drought in North Korea and its potential impact on food supplies in that country.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384179","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-30","<p>Below is a table showing total food and drink exports from the UK from 2000 to 2014. Included are the percentages of total UK exports each year that are exported to EU countries and EU Free Trade Association countries.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Total food and drink exports from the UK (£000s)</p></td><td><p>Percentage of UK food and drink exports to EU countries</p></td><td><p>Percentage of UK food and drink exports to EU Free Trade Association countries</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2000</p></td><td><p>8,378,287</p></td><td><p>62%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001</p></td><td><p>8,214,282</p></td><td><p>62%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2002</p></td><td><p>8,603,872</p></td><td><p>64%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2003</p></td><td><p>9,550,913</p></td><td><p>65%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2004</p></td><td><p>9,386,712</p></td><td><p>65%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005</p></td><td><p>9,626,612</p></td><td><p>65%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2006</p></td><td><p>10,141,048</p></td><td><p>66%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>10,976,473</p></td><td><p>67%</p></td><td><p>1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>12,711,889</p></td><td><p>68%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>13,445,210</p></td><td><p>68%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>15,194,264</p></td><td><p>65%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>17,455,367</p></td><td><p>63%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>17,347,316</p></td><td><p>61%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>17,956,542</p></td><td><p>60%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>17,915,031</p></td><td><p>60%</p></td><td><p>2%</p></t