"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383770","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills has received a number of written representations from current and former sub-postmasters, both in direct correspondence and through correspondence received via hon Members, regarding Post Office Limited’s Complaint Review and Mediation Scheme. This is an operational matter for Post Office Limited and the Scheme has been set up to be independent of Government.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-06-23T14:00:22.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383770/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383770/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-18","Sub Post Offices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what representations his Department has received from current and former sub-postmasters on the performance of the Post Office sub-postmaster mediation scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383771","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-23","<p>Post Office Limited’s Complaint Review and Mediation Scheme was set up in 2013 to consider cases from current and former subpostmasters relating to the Post Office Horizon IT system. This is an operational matter for Post Office Limited and the Scheme has been set up to be independent of Government.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-06-23T14:28:50.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383771/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383771/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-18","Sub Post Offices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the Post Office sub-postmaster mediation scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3258"
