"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383773","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-25","<p>The Minister for the Cabinet Office has received no such representations. This issue concerns the Lord Lyon King of Arms in his judicial capacity and is therefore a devolved matter.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","2991","2015-06-25T16:49:50.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383773/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383773/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-18","Airdrieonians Football Club","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent representations he has received on the decision of Lord Lyon to prevent Airdrieonians Football Club from using its current badge; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","3274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383774","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-26","<p>This answer covers the private offices of the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster, Minister for the Cabinet Office and Paymaster General, Parliamentary Under Secretary (Minister for Civil Society), Parliamentary Under Secretary (Minister for Constitutional Reform) and the Parliamentary Under Secretary for the Cabinet Office.</p><p> </p><p>The total number of staff employed in these offices is SCS1 x 1, Band A x 4, Band B2 x 5, Band B1 x 8, Band C x 3.</p><p> </p><p>The Cabinet Office pay bands for each grade are as follows:</p><p> </p><p>SCS1 £62,000 - £117,800</p><p> </p><p>Band A £46,000 - £60,484</p><p> </p><p>B2 £30,117 - £38,484</p><p> </p><p>B1 £23,793 - £30,093</p><p> </p><p>C £19,790 - £24,430</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-06-26T09:48:47.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383774/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383774/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-18","Cabinet Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many full-time equivalent staff of each civil service grade are employed in the private office of each Minister of his Department; and what the pay band of each such member of staff is.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","3165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383775","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-23","<p>Turnout is affected by a wide range of factors and cannot therefore be forecast with any degree of accuracy.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-06-23T15:54:29.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383775/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383775/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-18","Voting Rights: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect of extending the franchise in all elections to 16 and 17 year olds on voter turnout.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","3147"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383776","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Cabinet Office occupies 35 Great Smith Street, 10 Great George Street and Rosebery Court under leases held directly by the Cabinet Office with private landlords. These properties were rented before May 2010.</p><p>Our work to rationalise the Government's property estate has resulted in the exit of 2,018 buildings since 2010, raising £1.4 billion in capital receipts and generating £625 million in running costs savings up to 31 March 2014.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-06-24T16:19:57.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383776/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383776/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-18","Cabinet Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which buildings occupied by his Department are owned or part-owned privately; what the total value is of the rent paid to private landlords for the use of such buildings for official duties; and to whom such rent is paid.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383777","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-24","<p>For the local authority area of Renfrewshire, information detailing the number of families in receipt of Tax Credits can be found in the publication ‘Child and Working Tax Credits statistics finalised annual awards - geographical analysis’ available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics" target="_blank"><br> gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information relating to Child Benefit is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications" target="_blank">gov.uk/government/publications</a> by searching for publications named ‘Child Benefit geographical analysis’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","3138 ; 3143 ; 3173","2015-06-24T13:51:18.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383777/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383777/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Child Tax Credit: Renfrewshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many households were in receipt of child tax credit in Renfrewshire (a) on the last date for which figures are available and (b) in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","3091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383778","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs has no current plans to make an assessment on the UK economy of removing all customs duties on products from Africa.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-23T14:06:45.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383778/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383778/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Import Duties: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if his Department will make an assessment on the UK economy of removing all custom duties on products from Africa.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","3151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383779","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Government’s position on this issue was set out during the Westminster Hall debate on this topic on 17 March 2015.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T16:10:44.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383779/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383779/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Alcoholic Drinks: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will reduce the rate of VAT on (a) alcohol sold in the hospitality sector and (b) alcohol served with a meal in the hospitality sector.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","3088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383780","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-24","<p>HM Treasury rents space in three buildings: Rosebery Court, Norwich; Eastcheap Court, London and Melville Crescent, Edinburgh. In each case, the space is rented from other Government departments: Cabinet Office, Debt Management Office and Scotland Office respectively. HM Treasury pays a service charge for each of these occupations, which include rent, rates and maintenance. The below amounts were spent on occupation for the 2014/15 financial year:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Rosebery Court: £188,911.03;</p><p> </p><p>Eastcheap Court: £127,379.20; and</p><p> </p><p>Melville Crescent: £12,112.57.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-24T16:06:13.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383780/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383780/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Treasury: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which buildings occupied by his Department are owned or part-owned privately; what the total value is of the rent paid to private landlords for the use of such buildings for official duties; and to whom such rent is paid.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383781","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-25","<p>I can confirm that during the last five financial years from 2010-11 to 2014-15 that the department has not made any payments to the Institute of Fiscal Studies.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-25T14:41:21.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383781/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383781/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Treasury: Institute for Fiscal Studies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department made any payments to the Institute of Fiscal Studies in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mhairi Black","Paisley and Renfrewshire South","Ms Mhairi Black","3119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383782","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) produces the UK’s official economic forecasts. The Bank of England Inflation Reports also publish an estimate of spare capacity in the UK economy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-23T13:06:27.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383782/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383782/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent estimate his Department has made of the level of spare capacity in the economy; and on what analysis that estimate is based.","false","Biography information for George Kerevan","East Lothian","George Kerevan","3067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383783","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) published its latest tax gap estimates on 16 October 2014 in 'Measuring Tax Gaps' 2014 edition.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC do not break down any of the estimates by country.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T16:09:36.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383783/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383783/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Income Tax: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the income tax gap in Scotland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","3046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383784","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility regularly publishes its assessment of the fiscal impact of financial interventions in its Economic and Fiscal Outlook. The publications can be viewed online at <a href="http://www.budgetresponsibility.org.uk/" target="_blank">www.budgetresponsibility.org.uk</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In announcing the sale of the Government’s shareholding in Royal Bank of Scotland, the Chancellor is acting on independent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England and a report from Rothschild investment bank that it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to sell its stake. The report by Rothschild, and the corresponding advice from the Governor, are both available online at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","3134","2015-06-24T16:04:56.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383784/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383784/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on the public purse of the overall cost of intervention in UK banks following the financial crisis of 2007-08.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","3133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383785","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility regularly publishes its assessment of the fiscal impact of financial interventions in its Economic and Fiscal Outlook. The publications can be viewed online at <a href="http://www.budgetresponsibility.org.uk/" target="_blank">www.budgetresponsibility.org.uk</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In announcing the sale of the Government’s shareholding in Royal Bank of Scotland, the Chancellor is acting on independent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England and a report from Rothschild investment bank that it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to sell its stake. The report by Rothschild, and the corresponding advice from the Governor, are both available online at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/" target="_blank">www.gov.uk</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","3133","2015-06-24T16:04:56.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383785/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383785/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made in each of the last five years of the effect on the public purse of the sale of the Government's stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","3134"
