"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383790","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-25","<p>Estimates of the number of households where an individual is in receipt of married couples allowance are not available.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-25T16:25:34.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383790/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383790/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Married People: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many households received the married couple's allowance in Renfrewshire (a) on the last day for which figures are available and (b) in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","3174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383791","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-25","<p>The Government has a clear mandate to improve Britain’s relationship with the rest of the EU, and to reform the EU so that it creates jobs and increases living standards for all its citizens. As the Chancellor of the Exchequer has noted, the best outcome for the UK economy is that we achieve major economic reform of the EU. The Prime Minister is focused on success: he believes he can and will succeed in reforming and renegotiating our relationship with the EU and campaigning to keep the UK in the EU on that basis.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-25T15:04:20.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383791/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383791/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect on the economy of UK membership of the EU and what effect leaving the EU would have on the economy.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","3239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383792","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-02","<p>The government committed to providing free, impartial guidance through Pension Wise, to help people make informed and confident decisions about how they use their defined contribution pension savings in retirement. It is available online, via the telephone and face to face.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As of 6 April – the date on which the new pension flexibilities commenced – Pension Wise had handled more than 3,600 calls since the opening of the contact centre in late March. Nearly 1400 people had booked a telephone guidance appointment with the Pensions Advisory Service, while nearly 380 people had booked a face to face appointment with Citizens Advice. Citizens Advice does not provide Pension Wise guidance over the phone.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information on Pension Wise service usage since 6 April will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Pension Wise recommends that users take their time to prepare and gather relevant information before their guidance session, if they have not already done so by the time of booking their appointment; this can normally take around 2 weeks. The government estimates that, on average, face to face appointments take place within 9 days of booking.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","1071","2015-07-02T16:40:27.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383792/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383792/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Pensions: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people have received (a) face to face and (b) telephone advice through Pension Wise since that service opened; and what those numbers are as proportions of all people eligible to take advantage of new pension flexibilities.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383793","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>The government published a response to the House of Lords review of Personal Service Companies on the 9 June 2014.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T13:27:30.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383793/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383793/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Tax Avoidance: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2015 to Question 1914, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the implementation of IR35  anti-avoidance legislation.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383794","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>There is no statutory definition of a personal service company. For this reason it is not possible to provide a reliable estimate of the number of personal service companies who paid corporation tax<strong>.</strong></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-23T13:24:51.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383794/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383794/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Income Tax: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 15 June 2015 to Question 1915, what the total revenue collected in corporation tax for personal service companies was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383795","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-25","<p>No such estimate has been made.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In line with government and OFCOM guidance, HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has migrated all of its customer-facing 0845 helplines to 03 numbers, resulting in significant savings for its customers.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-25T15:07:15.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383795/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383795/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Revenue and Customs: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the potential cost to the public purse of converting HM Revenue and Customs helpline numbers to Freephone services.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","3221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383796","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-25","<p>This Government is committed to delivering a long-term, coherent, and sustainable framework for household energy efficiency. By April 2015, around 1.5 million energy efficiency measures were installed in well over a million properties with the Energy Company Obligation (ECO) delivering 97%. As part of this commitment we have extended ECO from March 2015 to 2017.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-25T13:11:05.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383796/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383796/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-18","Energy: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will fund a major retrofit programme for energy efficiency; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","3227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383797","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Government created a new, tough City regulator, the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), to protect customers and ensure Britain’s banks conduct themselves to the highest standards. The FCA has been in contact with Royal Bank of Scotland (RBS) regarding the recent IT issue affecting customer payments, and worked closely with the bank to resolve the problem. The payments issue has now been resolved, and the regulator will continue to work with RBS to diagnose and fix the root cause of the problem.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-23T14:47:04.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383797/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383797/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-18","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has made to the Royal Bank of Scotland on ensuring (a) pensioners and (b) other customers receive payments on time.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","3228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383798","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-26","<p>Whilst there is no specific duty on local authorities to promote community cohesion, they clearly must show due regard to the need to tackle discrimination and foster good relations between people.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-26T13:22:39.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383798/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383798/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Community Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that local councils uphold their statutory duty to promote community cohesion.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","3050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383799","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-10","<p>Since 2010 the Department has had considerable success in reducing the cost of its estate. We have saved:</p><p> </p><ul><li>£16 million per year by surrendering seven leasehold offices;</li><li>£24 million per year for Government by moving the Department to Marsham Street;</li><li>£10.9 million per year by subletting surplus leasehold office space.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2015-07-10T13:21:11.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383799/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383799/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Department for Communities and Local Government: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, which buildings occupied by his Department are owned or part-owned privately; what the total value is of the rent paid to private landlords for the use of such buildings for official duties; and to whom such rent is paid.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383800","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-23","<p>Officials have met with a number of housing associations on an individual basis and further meetings are planned.<br><br>Details of Ministers’ meetings and those of the Permanent Secretary with external organisations are published on-line here:<br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data</strong></a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dclg-permanent-secretary-data-2014#history" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dclg-permanent-secretary-data-2014#history</strong></a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-23T11:50:26.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383800/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383800/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with (a) housing associations and (b) lenders on the potential effects of the extension of the right to buy scheme on the credit ratings and ability to access credit of housing associations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","3189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383801","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-23","<p>The development of the policy is ongoing, and details will be set out in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","3188","2015-06-23T13:24:14.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383801/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383801/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Right to Buy Scheme: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will estimate the average loss to housing associations in (a) rental income over a period of 25 years and (b) capital for each housing association property sold under the proposed extension of the right to buy scheme in Warrington.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","3187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383802","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-23","<p>The development of the policy is ongoing, and details will be set out in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","3187","2015-06-23T13:24:14.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383802/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383802/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Right to Buy Scheme: Warrington","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many properties in (a) Warrington and (b) Warrington North constituency will qualify for sale to existing tenants under the proposed extension of the right to buy scheme to housing association tenants; and if he will estimate the average price on the open market of those properties.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","3188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383803","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-24","<p>Statistics on additional affordable housing provided in each local authority area in England are published in the Department’s live tables 1006 (social rent), 1006a (affordable rent), 1007 (intermediate housing) and 1008 (all affordable housing), which are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply</p><p> </p><p>These figures include both newly built housing and acquisitions.<br><br>Statistics are not compiled on the basis of parliamentary constituencies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-06-24T11:34:30.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383803/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383803/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-18","Affordable Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many affordable homes have been built in (a) Ribble Valley constituency, (b) Lancashire and (c) the UK since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","3202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383804","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport has not made any estimate of the number of libraries that will close in England and Wales between 2015 and 2020. It is a matter for local authorities to determine how best to provide a comprehensive and efficient public library service to their local community, within available resources. The Secretary of State’s duty is to superintend, and promote the improvement of, the public library service provided by local authorities in England only. Along with the Local Government Association, we have put in place a libraries’ taskforce to provide leadership and to help invigorate the public library service in England.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T14:01:47.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383804/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383804/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","Public Libraries: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of libraries that will close in England and Wales between 2015 and 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","3184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383805","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>I am currently considering a range of options for reviewing the BBC's Royal Charter and will make an announcement in due course.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T14:01:09.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383805/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383805/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","BBC: Royal Charters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, on what date he expects the review of BBC Charter renewal to commence.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","3136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383806","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-29","<p>According to Ofcom's Infrastructure Report 2014 coverage from all four mobile network operators (MNOs) is the same for Copeland and Cumbria. Specifically, 90% of premises have 2G coverage, 61% have 3G coverage and none have 4G coverage. Improving mobile coverage is a priority for the Government and as a result of the Government's landmark agreement with the MNOs in December 2014 each MNO will provide voice and text coverage to at least 90% of the UK landmass by 2017. Furthermore, as part of its 4G licence condition Telefonica is required to provide indoor coverage to at least 98% of UK premises by 2017. These measures will significantly improve mobile coverage in the UK.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-29T11:40:11.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383806/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383806/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383806/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","Mobile Broadband: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate his Department made of the proportion of (a) Copeland and (b) Cumbria covered by (i) 2G voice and low data rate mobile coverage, (ii) 3G high-speed data mobile coverage and (iii) 4G very high-speed data mobile coverage.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","3245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383807","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-26","<p>No staff in DCMS are paid less than the living wage.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-26T10:10:53.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383807/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383807/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383807/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many and what proportion of staff in his Department are paid less than the living wage.","false","Biography information for John Nicolson","East Dunbartonshire","John  Nicolson","3211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383808","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-07-23","<p>The Department for Culture, Media and Sport occupies one building that is owned or part-owned privately.The total rent per annum is £718,500 and is paid to Lazai Investment Ltd.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-07-23T17:08:56.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383808/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383808/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383808/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which buildings occupied by his Department are owned or part-owned privately; what the total value is of the rent paid to private landlords for the use of such buildings for official duties; and to whom such rent is paid.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383809","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-29","<p>Government will use information from a variety of sources and engagement with relevant parties to develop a target that we would expect to see reached by mid-2016. That information includes the Action on Hearing Loss, Sense and RNIB paper (April 2015). We have been monitoring progress of the provision of access services for Video on Demand content since 2013 through engagement with The Authority for Television On Demand (ATVOD), platform operators and content providers. Discussions with those parties are also helping us to understand better the technical challenges in providing such services.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-29T11:43:25.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383809/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383809/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383809/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-18","Video on Demand: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 12 June 2015 to Question 1237 on television: disability, what targets his Department uses to judge if significant progress has been made on the provision of access service on Video on Demand.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","3145"
