"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383812","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>Full details of the Gurkha mixed marriage compensation scheme will be published shortly. Gurkha veterans who think they qualify for the scheme are able to register their interest in the scheme and details of how to register can be found by searching 'Gurkha mixed marriage' on the gov.uk website.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:11:03.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383812/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383812/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383812/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Gurkhas: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to publish the details of the Gurkha mixed marriage compensation scheme.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","3066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383813","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>This information is not available as requested and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:09:08.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383813/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383813/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which buildings occupied by his Department are owned or part-owned privately; what the total value is of the rent paid to private landlords for the use of such buildings for official duties; and to whom such rent is paid.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383814","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>Between 1 April 2014 and 31 March 2015, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has reported that 27 laptops were lost. No desktop or tablet computers were reported as lost during this period.</p><p>The MOD treats all losses of assets seriously. All reported losses are subjected to an initial security risk assessment, with further action taken on a proportionate basis.</p><p>It is MOD policy that its laptops are encrypted to minimise the impact if a loss were to occur.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-24T16:11:43.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383814/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383814/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Ministry of Defence: Lost Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) desktop, (b) laptop and (c) tablet computers were lost by his Department in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","3048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383815","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>The UK has provided a range of non-lethal equipment to Ukraine. I refer the hon. Member to the statement I made on 6 March 2015 (Official Report, column 83WS) and the statement made on 17 October 2014 (Official Report, column 55WS). I regularly discuss support to Ukraine with NATO and EU counterparts and expect to do so at the next NATO Defence Ministers meeting on 24-25 June. Officials continue to engage with the Ukraine Ministry of Defence and Armed Forces on further requirements including the provision of training and wider support.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","3054 ; 3055","2015-06-23T16:26:15.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383815/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383815/answer","20150306_WMS_Support_to_Ukraine.doc ; 20141017_WMS_Gifting_of_non-lethal_Equipment_to_Ukraine.doc","20150306_WMS_Support_to_Ukraine.doc ; 20141017_WMS_Gifting_of_non-lethal_Equipment_to_Ukraine.doc","WMS - 6 March 2015 - Support to Ukraine ; WMS - 17 Oct 2014 - Gifting of non-lethal Eqpt","WMS - 6 March 2015 - Support to Ukraine ; WMS - 17 Oct 2014 - Gifting of non-lethal Eqpt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383815/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Ukraine: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to Paragraph 12 of the European Parliament resolution on the situation in Ukraine (2014/2965(RSP)), if he will take steps to provide (a) communications equipment, (b) night vision equipment and range finders and (c) other non-lethal military equipment to Ukraine; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","3053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383816","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>The UK has provided a range of non-lethal equipment to Ukraine. I refer the hon. Member to the statement I made on 6 March 2015 (Official Report, column 83WS) and the statement made on 17 October 2014 (Official Report, column 55WS). I regularly discuss support to Ukraine with NATO and EU counterparts and expect to do so at the next NATO Defence Ministers meeting on 24-25 June. Officials continue to engage with the Ukraine Ministry of Defence and Armed Forces on further requirements including the provision of training and wider support.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","3053 ; 3055","2015-06-23T16:26:15.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383816/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383816/answer","20150306_WMS_Support_to_Ukraine.doc ; 20141017_WMS_Gifting_of_non-lethal_Equipment_to_Ukraine.doc","20150306_WMS_Support_to_Ukraine.doc ; 20141017_WMS_Gifting_of_non-lethal_Equipment_to_Ukraine.doc","WMS - 6 March 2015 - Support to Ukraine ; WMS - 17 Oct 2014 - Gifting of non-lethal Eqpt","WMS - 6 March 2015 - Support to Ukraine ; WMS - 17 Oct 2014 - Gifting of non-lethal Eqpt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383816/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Ukraine: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with Ukraine on providing forces in that country with non-lethal military equipment.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","3054"
