"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383818","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>The Royal Navy uses a variety of fuels to sustain maritime commitments, with the process of forecasting fuel requirements forming an essential part of logistical support.</p><p> </p><p>The table below sets out the figures for estimated and actual fuel usage by the Royal Navy in support of maritime tasking over the last five years:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Calendar Year</p></td><td><p>Estimated Fuel Use</p><p>(in Cubic Meters)</p></td><td><p>Actual Fuel Use</p><p>(in Cubic Meters)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>265,954</p></td><td><p>256,254</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>232,884</p></td><td><p>221,418</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>233,872</p></td><td><p>188,387</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>214,771</p></td><td><p>192,104</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>191,358</p></td><td><p>176,267</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-24T15:30:19.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383818/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383818/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383818/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Navy: Fuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department made in each of the last five years of how much fuel would be needed in that year to accomplish all Royal Navy maritime tasking; and how much fuel was provided to the fleet in each such year.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","3047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383819","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-24","<p>The infrastructure work at RAF Marham is due to commence at the end of 2015.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-24T16:08:38.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383819/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383819/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383819/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2015 to Question 1740, whether infrastructure work in advance of the arrival of the F-35 squadron has begun at RAF Marham.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383820","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>In the Queen's Speech on 27 May 2015, the Government made clear its intention to conduct a full Strategic Defence and Security Review. Led by the Cabinet Office, the Government will consult with interested parties including Parliamentarians to inform our decision-making.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","3241","2015-06-23T16:20:00.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383820/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383820/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383820/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Strategic Defence and Security Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will consult political parties which are not in government on development of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","3250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383821","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 2 September 2013, (Official Report, column 39W), to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-25T15:21:40.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383821/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383821/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383821/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2015 to Question 1740, what complex weapons he expects to be operational on the F-35 (a) by 2018, (b) by 2019, (c) by 2020 and (d) after 2020.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","3213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383822","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>In the Queen's Speech on 27 May 2015, the Government made clear its intention to conduct a full Strategic Defence and Security Review. Led by the Cabinet Office, the Government will consult with interested parties, including businesses. The Ministry of Defence is leading on engagement with the defence industry.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-23T16:21:43.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383822/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383822/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383822/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Strategic Defence and Security Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to consult businesses as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","3252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383823","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review is being coordinated by the Cabinet Office with close engagement with all relevant Government Departments.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-23T16:21:06.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383823/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383823/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383823/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Strategic Defence and Security Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how he plans to liaise with other government departments on the development of the Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","3253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383824","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>I have already placed in the Library the summary of the independent report into the Libyan training at Bassingbourn. There are a number of sensitivities surrounding the documents relating to the meetings and Ministry of Defence officials are currently engaging with Departments across Government and with the Libyan Embassy, to consider whether they can be released. If they are deemed releasable I will place copies in the Library of the House in due course.</p><p>I would also like to refer the hon. Member to the written statement made by the previous Defence Secretary (Philip Hammond) on 11 June 2014 (Official Report, column 49-50WS) and the written statements made by the Defence Secretary (Michael Fallon) on 4 November 2014 (Official Report, column 44WS), and 9 January 2015 (Official Report, column 18WS) in relation to the Libyan General Purpose Force.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","3198","2015-06-23T16:40:00.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383824/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383824/answer","20140611_WMS_Training_Libyan_Troops_in_the_UK.doc ; 20141104_WMS_Libya_Update.doc ; 20150109_WMS_Libya_Training_Report.doc","20140611_WMS_Training_Libyan_Troops_in_the_UK.doc ; 20141104_WMS_Libya_Update.doc ; 20150109_WMS_Libya_Training_Report.doc","WMS - 11 Jun14 Training Libyan Troops in the UK ; WMS - 4 Nov 14 Libya Update ; WMS - 9 Jan 15 Libya Training Report","WMS - 11 Jun14 Training Libyan Troops in the UK ; WMS - 4 Nov 14 Libya Update ; WMS - 9 Jan 15 Libya Training Report","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/383824/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-18","Libya: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library notes and minutes of meetings between representatives of his Department and Cambridge City councillors on the effect on 